calEvent.description:
Holly Gramazio (game designer turned novelist) and Jim Munroe (novelist turned game designer) chat about writing, games, fiction, Jim's new graphic novel Zeroed Out, Holly's book about an attic full of endlessly spawning husbands -- and how The Husbands has been greenlit by Apple to be made into a TV series by A24 starring Juno Temple (Ted Lasso). Books on sale by Another Story.

Toronto Video Game Month is set to bring the world of gaming to life! From adrenaline-pumping esports tournaments to massive outdoor games played under the open sky, this event is designed for all—from hardcore gamers to the game-curious. Immerse yourself in interactive experiences, discover the talent of Toronto’s local indie developers, and engage with major studio activations. Plus, tap into the industry at a prestigious video game conference, thought-provoking workshops, and expert talks on the future of gaming. It’s a month to discover, play, and connect with Toronto’s thriving gaming community!

calEvent.description:
Join CYBEX and storyteller (and parent of two!) Sarain Fox for a community event to support maternal mental health and combat postpartum loneliness.

Did you know that 82% of pregnant and postpartum individuals experience loneliness? This isolation can seriously affect their mental health - and in turn, their child’s well-being. So, for this Maternal Mental Health Month, let’s change that, one step at a time.

Bring your little ones and come out for a leisurely walk, meet other parents, connect with host Sarain Fox, and build community together. CYBEX will donate $100 per registered walk (up to $10,000) to the charity Life With a Baby and all participants will be entered to win one of five prize packages.

calEvent.description: You can learn a lot about a city through the stories of the athletes it has celebrated and cheered on. Toronto’s past is filled with dramatic tales of sports heroes who have brought us championships and heartbreak – and shaped our city in the process. In this walk, we’ll trace that history through downtown Toronto and the waterfront, visiting long-lost stadiums, exploring Edwardian victory parades and uncovering stories of forgotten glories. Discover inspiring tales about icons – from Tom Longboat to Terry Fox, and Babe Ruth to Joe Carter – and learn about the impact their athletic exploits have had on the city’s identity.
calEvent.eventName: The Triumphs & Tragedies of Toronto's Sports Icons
